name: CoreAPI Run_Applications
description: API to access results of Planet 9 Run_Applications Details
about:
Description

The CoreAPI Run_Applications API enables to view which application are running (enabled) in the system and also enable/disable applications. You can see this also in the Application Management tool.

Prerequisites: In order for the API to work, you will have to change the endpoint in the General tab.

Operations  performed

Important note: Please review the definitions and the request/response bodies for each operation. In certain definitions, you will a description next each field. If not, view the example data in the selected operation.

/List

Get the list of all applications. Within each object in the returned array, the UUID of each item is placed. This is the same value that /State operation requires.

In the example data, you will find the response body of this operation.

Body

Retrieve the groups details corresponding to the UUID and other values.
